content: Made it from NYC to Israel!!! My first story airs tonight at 11pm.  As soon as I got off the plane in Tel Aviv, we drove to Jerusalem to work on the piece. I saw a lot of American flags up along the way in preparation for President Trump's arrival tomorrow.... which also made me feel right at home!! More to come on his visit over the next few days... üá∫üá∏üáÆüá± CBS New York

content: What an incredible day it has been in Israel! We jammed a lot in ... luckily getting to the Old City of Jerusalem before security shut it down ahead of President Trump's arrival. It was amazing to see the Western Wall, the holiest site for the Jewish people. It was also incredibly moving to actually physically see the 5th Station of the Cross.  I got to put my hand where it's believed Jesus Christ did while carrying the cross.  I'll be on at 5, 6, and 11pm tonight CBS New York

content: NYPD: officer in critical condition after being dragged by a car during a hit and run in East Flatbush, Brooklyn. Shortly after, police say a 15yo suspect walked into Brookdale Hospital with a gunshot wound. It appears the officer fired his gun twice while being dragged. Police say officers were initially investigating 911 calls of shots fired, but they determined the likely cause was fireworks. The officer hurt is a 9-year veteran and a married father of a 2yo.  Stay with CBS New York and Ali Bauman for the latest.
